  "description": "This is a perfect recipe for an air fryer and a busy week or a big gathering. You suffer once rolling dozens of tacos (or ask your friends to help!), but then you can warm them up quickly in an air fryer (for 5-6 minutes at 200C) or a skillet.\n\nTacos dorados are a humble Mexican street food that doesn't get the worldwide recognition it deserves. It usually comes as a side for [pozole](/recipes/pozole/) or tortas ahogadas, but they can be a dish on its own to feed a huge crowd, very practical to share at the table. \n\nHere we present only potatoes and cheese filling, but they can be done with variety of different filling, such as [refried beans](/recipes/frijoles-refritos/), chicken, meat, [picadillo](/recipes/picadillo/), fresh cheese (tvorog), or just vegetables.",
